import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; import { useSelector } from 'react-redux'; import { RootState } from '../store/store'; import { Users, Home, MessageSquare, Calendar, TrendingUp, CheckCircle, AlertCircle, Clock } from 'lucide-react'; const StaffDashboardPage: React.FC = () => { const { user } = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.auth); const [stats, setStats] = useState({ totalListings: 0, pendingVisits: 0, activeConversations: 0, completedTasks: 0 }); useEffect(() => { // Fetch staff-specific data fetchStaffStats(); }, []); const fetchStaffStats = async () => { try { // This would be implemented with actual API calls setStats({ totalListings: 45, pendingVisits: 12, activeConversations: 8, completedTasks: 23 }); } catch (error) { console.error('Error fetching staff stats:', error); } }; const quickActions = [ { title: 'Manage Visits', description: 'Schedule and manage property visits', icon: Calendar, color: 'bg-blue-500', href: '/visits' }, { title: 'Handle Messages', description: 'Respond to tenant inquiries', icon: MessageSquare, color: 'bg-green-500', href: '/messages' }, { title: 'Verify Listings', description: 'Review and verify property listings', icon: CheckCircle, color: 'bg-purple-500', href: '/listings/verify' }, { title: 'User Support', description: 'Assist users with platform issues', icon: Users, color: 'bg-orange-500', href: '/support' } ]; return (
